<p>
The Gentoo community uses Bugzilla (<uri
link="http://bugs.gentoo.org">bugs.gentoo.org</uri>) to record and track
bugs, notifications, suggestions and other interactions with the
development team.  Between 14 October 2007
and 20 October 2007, activity on the site has resulted in:
</p>

<ul>
<li>444 new bugs during this period</li>
<li>258 bugs closed or resolved during this period</li>
<li>16 previously closed bugs were reopened this period</li>
<li>79 closed as NEEDINFO/WONTFIX/CANTFIX/INVALID/UPSTREAM during this period</li>
<li>84 bugs marked as duplicates during this period</li>
</ul>

<p>
Of the 9763 currently open bugs: 15 are labeled 'blocker', 108 are labeled
'critical', and 334 are labeled 'major'.
</p>

